{"ID":270350, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"350\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs349.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs351.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 350<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">way, we begin to learn the only true God,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and what kind of a being we have got to worship. Having\n  a knowledge of God,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> we begin to know how to approach him,<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and how to ask so as to receive an\n  answer.<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> When we understand the character of God, and how to come to him,<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> he begins to unfold\n  the heavens to us,<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> and to tell us all about it.<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> When we are ready to come to him, he is ready to come\n  to us.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now, I ask all who hear me, why the learned men who are preaching salvation, say that God\n  created the heavens<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and the earth out of nothing? The reason is, that they are unlearned in the things\n  of God,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and have not the gift of the Holy Ghost;<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> they account it blasphemy in any one to\n  contradict their idea.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> If you tell them that God made the world out of something,<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> they will call\n  you a fool.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> But I am learned, and know more than all the world put together.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> The Holy Ghost\n  does, anyhow, and He is within me, and comprehends more than all the world:<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and I will associate\n  myself with Him.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Meaning of the Word Create<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">You ask the learned doctors why they say the world was made out of nothing; and they will\n  answer, &ldquo;Doesn&rsquo;t the Bible say He <i>created<\/i> the world?&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> And they infer, from the word create, that\n  it must have been made out of nothing. Now, the word create came from the word <i>baurau<\/i> which\n  does not mean to create out of nothing; it means to organize;<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> the same as a man would organize\n  materials and build a ship.<span class=\"textFootRef\">a<\/span> Hence, we<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108865\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108865)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108865)\">John 17:3<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112848\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112848)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112848)\">Ether 2:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113351\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113351)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113351)\">D&amp;C 20:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116391\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116391)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116391)\">D&amp;C 132:24<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106914\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106914)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106914)\">Prov. 2:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109363\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109363)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109363)\">Rom. 11:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109889\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109889)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109889)\">Col. 1:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112861\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112861)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112861)\">Ether 3:20<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114637\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114637)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114637)\">D&amp;C 84:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116187\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116187)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116187)\">D&amp;C 128:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107377\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107377)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107377)\">Jer. 30:21<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115019\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115019)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115019)\">D&amp;C 93:19-20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116032\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116032)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116032)\">D&amp;C 124:95<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110701\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110701)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110701)\">Rev. 3:20<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114982\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114982)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114982)\">D&amp;C 90:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108809\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108809)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108809)\">John 14:23<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116240\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116240)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116240)\">D&amp;C 130:3<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111415\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111415)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111415)\">Jacob 6:5<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114859\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114859)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114859)\">D&amp;C 88:63<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">9. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"105947\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 105947)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(105947)\">Gen. 1:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">10. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109430\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109430)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109430)\">1 Cor. 2:10-11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114391\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114391)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114391)\">D&amp;C 76:12<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116952\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116952)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116952)\">Moses 8:16<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">11. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109042\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109042)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109042)\">Acts 8:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"109150\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 109150)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(109150)\">Acts 19:2<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">12. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108266\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108266)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108266)\">Matt. 26:65<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108370\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108370)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108370)\">Mark 14:64<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108755\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108755)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108755)\">John 10:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111435\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111435)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111435)\">Jacob 7:7<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">13. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117063\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117063)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117063)\">Abr. 4:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">14. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108603\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108603)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108603)\">Luke 24:25<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111846\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111846)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111846)\">Alma 8:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112012\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112012)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112012)\">Alma 21:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112089\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112089)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112089)\">Alma 30:14<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">15. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117035\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117035)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117035)\">Abr. 3:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">16. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108805\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108805)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108805)\">John 14:16-17,26<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">17. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"105948\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 105948)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(105948)\">Gen. 1:1<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"105962\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 105962)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(105962)\">Gen. 2:4<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">18. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117064\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117064)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117064)\">Abr. 4:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n  <\/div>\n  <div class=\"textFootnotes\">\n    \n      <p class=\"std\"><span class=\"textMark\">a<\/span>The view of the Prophet on this subject of creation is abundantly sustained by men of learning subsequent to his time. The Rev Baden Powell, of Oxford University, for instance, writing for Kitto&rsquo;s <i>Cyclopaedia of Biblical Literature,<\/i> says: &ldquo;The meaning of this word (create) has been commonly associated with the idea of &lsquo;making out of nothing.&rsquo; But when we come to inquire more precisely into the subject, we can of course satisfy ourselves as to the meaning only from an examination of the original phrase.&rdquo; The learned professor then proceeds to say that three distinct Hebrew verbs are in different places employed with reference to the same divine act, and may be translated, respectively, &ldquo;create,&rdquo; &ldquo;make,&rdquo; &ldquo;form or fashion.&rdquo; &ldquo;Now,&rdquo; continues the Professor, &ldquo;though each of these has its shade of distinction, yet the best critics understand them as so nearly synonymous that, at least in regard to the idea of making out of nothing, little or no foundation for that doctrine can be obtained from the first of these words.&rdquo; And, of course, if no foundation for the doctrine can be obtained from the first of these words&mdash;viz., the verb translated &ldquo;create,&rdquo; then the chances are still less for there being any foundation for the doctrine of creation from nothing in the verb translated, &ldquo;made,&rdquo; &ldquo;formed,&rdquo; or &ldquo;fashioned.&rdquo;<\/p>\n      <p class=\"std\">Professor Powell further says: &ldquo;The idea of &lsquo;creation,&rsquo; as meaning abso-<\/p>\n    \n  <\/div>\n<\/div>"}